The influx of high-tech digital speed cameras has seen the the number of motorists trapped surge to 115,000 in the last year - the highest number since 2009.

Ministry of Justice figures show that a total of 115,549 motorists were fined at least £100 pounds by magistrates after being caught speeding.

The increase has been put down to the £10,000 digital cameras, that no longer require film and can operate 24 hours a day, the Telegraph reported.

