Hugh Bladon, one of the founding members of the Alliance of British Drivers, said: 'Speeding accounts for less than five per cent of accidents and only takes into account one aspect of how people are driving.

'They (speed cameras) do not measure whether the driver is under the influence of drink or drugs or how roadworthy their vehicle is. What about the other aspects?'  

